==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Maori]]. Literal translation: "Long White Cloud" (''ao'' = cloud/daytime/world ''tea'' = white, ''roa'' = long/tall). Often translated as "The land of the long white cloud". Probably a reference to the appearance of mountainous land when seen on the horizon from a canoe after an ocean voyage. Allegedly the first English language mention was in the [[February]] 1916 New Zealand School Journal (King, 2004).

